;;; The following rule shows a more complex NAC that also includes negative nodes. As before, the first NAC ensures that a _new_ edge is created. The second NAC models a (hypothetical) constraint that a parent_of relationship may only be created for a child who does not already have (at least) two parents.  (Note that the rule matching semantcis is defined as _isomorphic_ to enforce that _n1_ and _n2_ match different nodes. This is explained below.)
