;; **
;;; ## Path Expressions
;;; 
;;; Sometimes we want to describe a pattern that involves nodes connected by an arbitrary number of edges. This can be done using _path expressions_. Consider the following rule that finds any node that can be reached by traversing any edges a _Person_ node with a given name.
;; **

;; @@
(rule 'related-to ['name]
      :read (pattern (node 'p :label "Person" :asserts {:name "'&name'"})
                     (node 'a)
                     (path "-*" :src 'p :tar 'a)))
